<subSubSection pageId="177" pageNumber="178" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="177" pageNumber="178">
This species ranges from southern Minnesota (Gandhi et al. 2005: 922) to the Pacific Coast in southern California, south to the state of Oaxaca in Mexico (Gidaspow 1959: 269). The records from Missouri (probably based on the type locality of 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triste">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Calosoma triste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Arkansas”">&quot;Arkansas&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Burgess and Collins 1917: 87), possibly based on a stray, need confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
